law.text:
The Department may revoke any discharge permit if the Department finds that:
False or inaccurate information was contained in the application;
Conditions or requirements of the discharge permit have been or are about to be violated;
Substantial deviation from plans, specifications, or requirements has occurred;
The Department has been refused entry to the premises for the purpose of inspecting to insure compliance with the conditions of the discharge permit;
A change in conditions exists that requires temporary or permanent reduction or elimination of the permitted discharge;
Any State or federal water quality stream standard or effluent standard has been or is threatened to be violated; or
Any other good cause exists for revoking the discharge permit.
